HEADWORD: Commissariat
<hw>Com`mis*sa"ri*at</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>commissariat</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
organized system by which armies and military posts are supplied with
food and daily necessaries.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The body of officers
charged with such service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

